# Codex Writer Findings — Unknown Chain: split-order-per-dish-x-s230-260407-112801-978b

## Findings
1. [P1] Fix 1 not implemented in `processHallOrder` — [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx`](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx) lines 3709-3747 still call `getNextOrderNumber(partner, 'hall')` once, create one `Order` with `total_amount: finalTotal`, then `bulkCreate` all cart lines under that single `order.id`. That preserves the old `1 Order + N OrderItems` model, so StaffOrdersMobile will still advance the whole order when a waiter accepts one dish. FIX: replace the single `Order.create` + `OrderItem.bulkCreate` block with the required per-cart-line loop, splitting `discount_amount` proportionally, preserving `quantity`, generating a unique `public_token` per order, calling `getNextOrderNumber` once per iteration, and updating `Partner` once with the final accumulated counters.
2. [P1] Fix 1 hall post-submit flow still assumes one order — [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx`](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx) lines 3775-3805 and 3810-3859 still route loyalty earn/update to `order.id`, cache only one `updatedCounters`, insert one optimistic order, attach every optimistic item to the same `order.id`, and pass `order.public_token` to `showConfirmation`. Even if the create block were split later, the local session state and confirmation token would still collapse the cart back to one hall order. FIX: switch loyalty and confirmation to `createdOrders[0]`, use `finalUpdatedCounters`, push all `createdOrders` into `setSessionOrders`, and create one optimistic item per created order using `createdOrders[i].id`.
3. [P1] Fix 2 not implemented in pickup/delivery submit path — [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx`](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx) lines 4094-4124 still build one `orderData`, call `Order.create` once, and `bulkCreate` all `OrderItem`s under that order. That leaves delivery/takeaway in the same forbidden `1 Order + N OrderItems` structure instead of `N` orders with one item each. FIX: replace this block with the specified per-cart-line loop, using shared base fields and per-item `total_amount`, `discount_amount`, and `public_token`, while keeping `order_number` and `split_type` absent.
4. [P1] Fix 2 delivery/takeaway post-submit flow is still single-order-only — [`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx`](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx) lines 4152-4170 and 4193-4199 still attach loyalty earn/update to `order.id` and use `order.public_token` for confirmation, and there is no N-order optimistic `setSessionOrders` / `setSessionItems` update after submit. That does not match the required first-order loyalty scoping and multi-order post-submit state for the split-order design. FIX: route loyalty side effects through `createdOrders[0]`, add the required N-order optimistic order/item updates without `guest` or `split_type`, and pass `createdOrders[0].public_token` to `showConfirmation`.

## Summary
Total: 4 findings (0 P0, 4 P1, 0 P2, 0 P3)

